The course introduces  the role of  the religion in the western culture through
* history of culture (literature, art, music ect),
* exploring religious background of Historical events,
* religious sociology (religious developments in history and nowadays)Objectives/eesmärkid:  Student acquires basic knowledge necessary to see and understand the impact of Religion in the formation of the westerns culture in the past and nowadays.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student: 1. Knows the the impact of religion in the history of European culture and correlates this knowledge with wider historical context; interprets the influence of religion and it's dynamics in contemporary western world.  2. Understands the impact of the Bible on upon the development of Western culture and society. 3. Knows the main Bible stories reflected in the art, music, literature and science and gives examples.
